        <h3>Jungle Temple</h3>
        <p>This level is meant to be spacious, allowing the player a sense of exploration. There are multiple paths and lots of nooks and crannies to explore. I wanted to give Mario sort of an Indiana Jones adventure.</p>
        <p><strong>In Hindsight</strong>: </p>
        <ul>
            <li>I wish I had implemented some switches here and there to make it feel like the player was unlocking the next part of the level, as if they're breaking into the temple.</li>
            <li>The custom tileset is a bit janky looking.</li>
            <li>The end of the level with the flag feels too out of place compared to the rest of the level.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>


